@{FG Shine}Welcome to AmiChannel News@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 15th issue of AmiChannel News.

Taking into account the sad events happend during last months, probably the best
news of the year is the final release of the long awaited AmigaOS 3.5.

The last revision of our beloved operating system was released six years ago,
in times of Commodore. Although Gateway owe us nothing, we have been waiting for
so long that I think we deserved this version to be released (even before it has
been).

Anyway, I am afraid that we are not going to see another revision of the OS
coming form Amiga Inc., perhaps some bug fixes or additions which were promised
but, for lack of time, have not been included in the final release (including
Miami 3.5 version).

The reason for this is that Gateway is not interested in our OS, so, why not
release the AmigaOS as open source? So far, there are two initiatives to
convince Gateway to do so. The question remains: why two and not only one? The
reason as always is politics. And if they do not work together they are going to
fail. But you never can tell.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located currently in:

         http://teleline.terra.es/personal/angelsau/index.html

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
