@node not06 "THE WORLD FOUNDRY: OCTOBER UPDATE"

                       THE WORLD FOUNDRY: OCTOBER UPDATE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TWF Update

Our website has had a few additions in September. Firstly, we have started
running regular opinion polls on our news page (thanks to a nice little rebol
script) and a new support section.

   * Opinion polls

        The first poll asked the question: "Should Explorer 2260 be made GFXcard
        only ?" We received a total of 81 votes and broke down into the 3
        possible choices as:

                Yes ............... 64
                No ................ 12
                Don't care ......... 5

        The second of our polls which is running at present asks the question:
        "What would your opinion be of a Linux version of Explorer2260 ?" with
        the choices being: "Good idea" "Bad idea" & "AAGGH! Noo!!! Don't do
        it!!" Last I looked the votes were divided roughly 75%, 8% & 17%
        respectively. The poll will be running for another week or so if you
        feel strongly enough about it, go to our site and cast your vote.

        We take into consideration the results of these polls but they won't be
        the deciding factor in decisions we make about our software line.

   * Support Section

        A support section has also been added to the website. This will be
        providing easy access to game patches but since we haven't finished the
        games yet, they won't be there for a while. :) The section will also
        cover additional programs we develop and wish to share with the
        visitors to the website.

        The first program to be offered in this section is the TWFCD player that
        was developed initially to test out the sound library used by E2260 but
        gradually developed into a proper CD player with track number pad,
        album/track display, loading/saving MCDP compatible cd files, link to
        the TWF website and a few other features. The TWFCD player is classed
        as freeware.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Explorer 2260 Update

Some more work done on E2260 this month. Still not back to full development with
external projects that just won't go away and Rob moving to NY causing
distruption in the GFX development. Maybe we'll be luckier in October. :)

Anyway, here is what happened in September:

   * Texturing system scrapped and replaced with 16bit version.
   * New network-friendly texture system developed.
   * New texture management tool in development.
   * Testing of sound subsystems complete.
   * Design of entity system enhanced to include multi-script activation on
     entity-specific events.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Maim & Mangle Update

Here is what has been done:

   * added collision detection routines (next step I'll add some sort of
     'physical reaction' when 2 or more units collide)
   * added a new experimental zsort - zbuffer routine
   * a few improvments to our editors
   * additional units designed and modeled and textures created

There are another couple of short articles in M&M in the November issue of Amiga
Format and the first issue of the new Amiga magazine AmigActive.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
More info at: www.worldfoundry.com
