@node not09 "IMAGE ENGINEER - FINALLY AN UPDATE (AND A NEW WEBSITE)"

             IMAGE ENGINEER - FINALLY AN UPDATE (AND A NEW WEBSITE)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From: Marko Seppänen <marko.seppanen@wwnet.fi>

Image Engineer is here again to stay..

Development of Image Engineer has been taker over by Wision, which is the group,
I (Marko Seppänen) am managing.

Last version of this image manipulation program from the original author, Simon
Edwards, was already very good. Sadly it never got famous enough. However some
dared to give Image Engineer a change to show its skills. Since then, they have
been active users of Image Engineer. I was of one them.

Image Engineer is unusual program. So called standards for image manipulation
programs already are set by the big players. Could you just believe that what
ever effect you apply to a whole image or a region, result will always appear in
form of a new image window? Well.. why should it work that way? I could tell you
many reasons, but as you know; 1 picture tells more than thousand stories. Take
a look at the new website of Image Engineer for some eye candy. There you can
also download updated Image Engineer-archives.

Details of next version of Image Engineer will be announced later. Development
has been running half speed, but now it's time to speed it up.

Marko Seppänen, Wision
