@node not27 "TABLEPLUG V1.1 HAS BEEN RELEASED"

                        TABLEPLUG V1.1 HAS BEEN RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From: Esteve Boix <stv@minorisa.es>

tablePlug is a MUI-based HTML image cataloguer. It will scan any directory and
will create the HTML files and the thumbnails so that you can use your browser
to navigate through the catalogs.

Features:

   * Easy to use, but *very configurable*: background images, colors, order of
     elements, which elements should be displayed and in what order, JavaScript
     events...
   * Generates HTML 3.2 compliant code.
   * Supports images and dirs in the same level.
   * Uses external ARexx programs to control image processing software to
     generate the thumbnails. Currently ArtEffect, TVPaint, GFXCon and
     ImageStudio are supported. More to come.
   * The user can tell tP to use diferent ARexx modules to create diferent
     image-types thumbnails.
   * The original images and the catalog files (HTML and thumbnails) may reside
     in diferent dirs.

Requires:

   * AmigaDOS v3.0+.
   * MUI v3.8.
   * BetterString.mcc (included in this distribution archive).
   * You should have the appropiate datatypes (JPEG/PNG) installed.

New for v1.1:

   * Solved the 'run from wb' problem.
   * tablePlug now uses placeholders for most of it's options.
   * Updated TPX information
   * Added JavaScript support.
   * Added <hr> options.
   * Added <br>s tag.
   * Added a 'Use existing HTML files' option.
   * tablePlug does not write unfinished pages if the process is stopped by the
     user (allowing the 'Use existing HTML files' options to work properly).
   * Added animation.datatype support to tP itself, not only tp_dtc.

For more information, please visit: www.esteveb.com

tablePlug is released as Shareware. The fee is _only_ $10, so please consider
registering it if you use it, and support the development of this program.
